    "cpap-body-6": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "cpap-heading-6": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How Is This Different From a Mouthpiece?",
            "title_highlight_1": "none",
            "title_highlight_2": "none",
            "heading_size": "h2",
            "alignment": "left",
            "mobile_alignment": "mobile-left",
            "margin_top": 21,
            "margin_bottom": 12
          }
        },
        "cpap-text-6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Dental mouthpieces (mandibular advancement devices) have been around for years. But they come with their own set of problems:</p><ul><li><strong>Jaw pain and TMJ issues</strong> — forcing the jaw forward from inside the mouth stresses the joint</li><li><strong>Teeth shifting</strong> — many users report permanent changes to their bite</li><li><strong>Drooling and discomfort</strong> — having a foreign object in your mouth all night is no better than a mask</li><li><strong>Expensive custom fittings</strong> — dentist-made devices can cost $2,000+</li></ul><p>AirwayPro™ works <strong>externally</strong>. It supports the jaw from the outside — no pressure on your teeth, no stress on your TMJ, nothing inside your mouth. It's the difference between pushing someone from behind versus grabbing them by the teeth.</p>",
            "alignment": "left",
            "mobile_alignment": "mobile-left",
            "text_size": 16,
            "margin_top": 9,
            "margin_bottom": 12
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "cpap-heading-6",
        "cpap-text-6"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "display_id": false,
        "visibility": "always-display",
        "full_width": false,
        "mobile_narrow_width": false,
        "color_scheme": "background-1",
        "padding_top": 12,
