    },
    "cpap-body-7": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "cpap-heading-7": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Travel, Camping, Power Outages — No Problem",
            "title_highlight_1": "none",
            "title_highlight_2": "none",
            "heading_size": "h2",
            "alignment": "left",
            "mobile_alignment": "mobile-left",
            "margin_top": 21,
            "margin_bottom": 12
          }
        },
        "cpap-text-7": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Think about the last time you traveled with your CPAP. The bulky case. Fighting for an outlet near the hotel bed. Explaining the machine to TSA. The panic when the power goes out during a storm.</p><p>AirwayPro™ weighs <strong>less than 4 ounces</strong>. It fits in a dopp kit. It requires <strong>zero electricity</strong>. Camping? No problem. Red-eye flight? No problem. Hurricane knocks out the power? You'll sleep fine while every CPAP user in the neighborhood is gasping.</p><p>\"I took mine to a music festival,\" says Sarah K., a 41-year-old user from Austin. \"Slept in a tent for three nights and woke up feeling better than I do at home with my CPAP. My friends couldn't believe it.\"</p>",
            "alignment": "left",
            "mobile_alignment": "mobile-left",
            "text_size": 16,
            "margin_top": 9,
            "margin_bottom": 12
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "cpap-heading-7",
        "cpap-text-7"
      ],
      "settings": {
